  "body": "### Description\n\nWhat would make the amazing `dev` experience even nicer would be the possibility to add different test \"profiles\" or \"suites\" that can be triggered via keystroke, besides the `r` for (re-)running the tests.\r\n\r\nExample: Run my unit tests (that I've defined with `.*UnitTest`) with pressing `t` and `1`, run my UI tests (defined with `.*UITest`) with `t` + `2`, and so on.\r\n\r\nRight now, I am running the `dev` mode in different versions of `quarkus.test.{exclude,include}-pattern`, but that requires a restart every time, I'm in a different \"testing mode\".\r\n\r\nHow we could do that is to define the different suites in the build Quarkus plugin section, or via property, such as `quarkus.test.suite[index].{exclude-include}-pattern` (`suite` only being a suggestion).\r\n\r\nWDYT?\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
